        <name xml:lang="en">sodium hydroxide, without water, in 50% solution state</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Calculated value based on stoichiometric calculations and literature data. 
39.997108g/mol is the molar mass of sodium hydroxide, without water, in 50% solution state (HNaO). 
222.240308g/mol is the molar mass of sodium cumenesulphonate (C9H11NaO3S). 

Sodium cumene sulphonate is produced by sulphonizing cumene with a solution of sulfuric acid, the resulting product is neutralized with the aid of sodium hydroxide (Franck and Stadelhofer 1987).
Chemical reaction:
C9H12 + H2SO4 + NaOH -&gt; C9H11NaO3S + 2H2O</comment>
